It's time to thoroughly renovate the bedroom. This is the last room in the house that was only minimally decorated.
Tear out the ugly electric fireplace and hearth. Seal the chimney, replace the cracked plaster, and repaint it. Get a custom closet made.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
A few dried-up dead birds were found behind the flue :(
Prepare for next week's plasterers
We're quite happy with the little nook next to it
Install the new closet here (we haven't even started designing yet🙈)
Haha, what did we find behind the radiator!
Remember adding the cute vent to prevent moisture in the chimney
Sweep the chimney cap and liner. Those magpies nesting in the chimney should be safer now. 🪺
The plasterers are done. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork pad is installed. I even used a toilet paper roll to make a part for the vacuum cleaner to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has been prepared, so we can start laying it now. Let's have a cup of tea and take a break.
Yeah, today's progress was a bit slow because we had to cut around the doorframes to match seamlessly with the hallway (which is also being laid with floor). It's very time-consuming. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me.
Finally finished, but everything looks messy! Even the assembly instructions for the new bed are terrible. Finally, I can sleep well tonight!
The corridor floor and baseboards are still unfinished. The decorators won't come for another month, so we're making do for now, with just bare plasterboard in the rooms.
Quick DIY job in the evening - trimmed part of the bottom of the doorframes with a tenon saw and chisel so the floor could fit perfectly underneath.
The cork underlay for the corridor is also in place.
We finished the corridor floor yesterday! This morning at 5 AM, we went to Heathrow Airport to pick up package number one, took a nap, and are finally ready to install the baseboards. Once the glue dries, we'll fill the gaps.
